1 as the benefit district and the same shall be fixed by the ordinance
2 authorizing and providing for the acquisition of the land or interest. The
3 governing body, as soon as practicable after passage of the ordinance
4 authorizing and providing for the appropriation of such land or interest and
5 the fixing of the benefit district, if any is fixed, shall proceed to exercise
6 the power of eminent domain in accordance with the eminent domain
7 procedure act.
8 (b) (1) The governing body of a city shall not approve the exercise of
9 eminent domain by such city unless each member of such governing body
10 whose district territory includes the land, either in whole or in part, that is
11 to be acquired by eminent domain votes in the affirmative to exercise
12 eminent domain to acquire such land.
13 (2) This subsection shall apply to the acquisition of land for the
14 purposes stated under any of the provisions of article 28 of chapter 19 of
15 the Kansas Statutes Annotated, and amendments thereto, regarding the
16 acquisition of land by counties through the exercise of eminent domain
17 and for any other public recreational purpose, including, but not limited
18 to, nature areas, entertainment venues, libraries and any other
19 recreational building or grounds that are not otherwise described in
20 article 28 of chapter 19 of the Kansas Statutes Annotated, and
21 amendments thereto.
22 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 26-201 is hereby repealed.
23 Sec. 4. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
24 publication in the statute book.

